The paper discusses the Mathematical Theory of Evidence (MTE) and its relationship to frequencies, which are concepts commonly studied in artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), statistics (cs.ST), information theory (cs.IT), and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper's focus on the weaknesses of various proposals of probabilistic interpretation also suggests a connection to these sub-categories.
